'''Leonard "Leon" Lucas''' (September 4, 1901 &ndash; May 1971) was an [[United States|American]] [[Boxing|boxer]] who competed in the [[1928 Summer Olympics]].

He was born and died in [[Camden, New Jersey]].

In 1928 he was eliminated in the first round of the [[Boxing at the 1928 Summer Olympics - Men's light heavyweight|light heavyweight class]] after losing his fight to the upcoming silver medalist [[Ernst Pistulla]].

